-- Tanzanian Government's Anti-Graft Agency Makes 17 Arrests, Daily News Says
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-07-27T06:35:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/tanzanian-government-s-anti-graft-agency-makes-17-arrests-daily-news-says.html

          
          
             Tanzanian authorities arrested 17
people on bribery charges after they allegedly doled out money,
garments and honey to win votes in October elections,  the Daily
News  reported, citing a  Prevention and Combating of Corruption
Bureau  official.  
 One of the apprehended, a female district commissioner, was
running to become lawmaker for the ruling  Chama Cha Mapinduzi 
party in the northern Kilimanjaro constituency, the state-run,
Dar es Salaam-based newspaper said today, citing regional PCCB
commander Alexander Budigila.  
 Presidential and legislative elections are scheduled in the
east African nation for Oct. 31, the newspaper said.  
